## Database Schema Strategy

### Entity Relationship Overview (Full System)

```mermaid
erDiagram
    PROFILES ||--o{ CATEGORIES : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ TAGS : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ ACCOUNTS : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ EXPENSES : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ INCOMES : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ SALARY_RECORDS : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ INVESTMENTS : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ GOALS : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ MILESTONES : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ NOTES : has
    PROFILES ||--o{ TIMELINE_EVENTS : has

    CATEGORIES ||--o{ EXPENSES : categorizes
    CATEGORIES ||--o{ INCOMES : categorizes
    CATEGORIES ||--o{ CATEGORIES : "parent of"

    ACCOUNTS ||--o{ EXPENSES : "paid from"
    ACCOUNTS ||--o{ INCOMES : "received in"

    EXPENSES }o--o{ TAGS : tagged
    INCOMES }o--o{ TAGS : tagged
    NOTES }o--o{ TAGS : tagged

    GOALS ||--o{ MILESTONES : contains
    GOALS }o--o{ INVESTMENTS : "linked to"
    GOALS }o--o{ NOTES : "linked to"

    EXPENSES ||--o{ ATTACHMENTS : has
    NOTES ||--o{ ATTACHMENTS : has
```

### Migration Naming Convention

```
YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_descriptive_name.sql

Example:
20260703000001_create_profiles.sql
20260703000002_create_categories.sql
20260703000003_create_accounts.sql
20260703000004_seed_default_categories.sql
```

---

## Key Design Decisions

### Why These Choices?

| Decision | Rationale |
|----------|-----------|
| **Next.js App Router** | Server components for performance, streaming, built-in API routes |
| **Supabase over custom backend** | Auth, DB, Storage, Realtime — all in one. Reduces DevOps overhead |
| **Row Level Security** | Security at the database level — even if API is compromised, data is safe |
| **Zustand over Redux** | Lightweight, minimal boilerplate, perfect for single-user app |
| **TanStack Query** | Server state management with caching, background refetching, optimistic updates |
| **Zod for validation** | Runtime type checking that integrates with TypeScript + React Hook Form |
| **NUMERIC(15,2) for money** | Avoids floating-point errors. Supports values up to ₹99,99,99,99,99,999.99 |
| **UUID primary keys** | Globally unique, safe for distributed systems, no sequential ID guessing |
| **`updated_at` triggers** | Database-level consistency — can't forget to update timestamps |
| **Soft deletes (future)** | Financial data should never be truly deleted — archival pattern |
| **Slugs for categories** | URL-friendly, human-readable, stable references |
| **`is_system` flag** | Prevents users from deleting default categories |

### Security Model

```mermaid
graph TD
    A["Request"] --> B{"Authenticated?"}
    B -->|No| C["Redirect to /login"]
    B -->|Yes| D{"Route Protected?"}
    D -->|No| E["Serve Public Page"]
    D -->|Yes| F["Next.js Middleware<br/>Verify Session"]
    F --> G{"Session Valid?"}
    G -->|No| C
    G -->|Yes| H["Serve Page"]
    H --> I["Supabase Query"]
    I --> J{"RLS Policy Check"}
    J -->|Pass| K["Return Data"]
    J -->|Fail| L["Empty Result / 403"]
```

